description: Laurina Fleure, 32, looked like she really knew how to party at the Glass Merchants Cafe Bar Launch Party on Tuesday.
title: The Bachelor's Laurina Fleure giddy at Melbourne event
title_page: The Bachelor's Laurina Fleure giddy at Melbourne event | Daily Mail Online
text:
She's the glamorous reality starlet known for her sassy sense of fashion.
And Laurina Fleure, 32, made sure she was the centre of attention as she stunned in an all-white ensemble at the Glass Merchants Cafe Bar Launch Party in Melbourne on Tuesday.
The socialite looked feminine and elegant in her high-necked white jumpsuit, which featured lace scalloped hem detailing and a fitted waist-band.
Now this is how you party! Laurina Fleure appeared giddy as she posed for photos alongside fellow Bachelor pal Amber Gelinas.
Her look was enhanced with a pair of chic snake skin heels and a leather wrist watch.
During the crowded event, she was seen chatting animatedly with fellow Bachelor pal Amber Gelinas, who appeared with her on season two of the franchise.
The ladies looked giddy after having a bit of fun on the dance floor, with Laurina perching herself up onto a high table.
Strike a pose! Both Laurina and Amber looked to be having their fair share of fun during the trendy party
White hot! Laurina looked elegant in her white jumpsuit, which featured lace detailing and a waist-band
Meanwhile, Amber showed off her curves in a violet floral number, pair with white strappy heels.
She first came to social media prominence on season two of The Bachelor, where she was dubbed the villain.
After missing out on romance with Blake Garvey, Laurina then went on to take part in the second season of I'm A Celebrity.... Get Me Out Of Here!
Reality TV star: After her stint on season two of the Bachelor, Laurina went on to take part in season two of I'm A Celebrity... Get Me Out Of Here!
She fast began to earn new fans on the show after the lovable beauty's villain persona was debunked during the series.
As a result of her new-found fandom, Laurina ended up placing third in the competition.
Since leaving her reality TV has amassed a following on social media with more than 60,000 on Instagram.
